The paper deals with concurrent games played on graphs, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also presents algorithmic solutions for these games, which involve combinatorial and computational techniques, making it relevant to the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
